    "display_name": "Fan Coil Monitoring",
    "description": "Classification of fan coil vibrations from still, low vibration to high vibration using the MLC.\n\nThis example allows you to monitor and classify the behavior of a fan, in particular those found on fan-coil HVAC units, but you can also try it on other kinds of rotating ventilation. Classification is based on motor vibration (high or low), in addition to providing an 'immobile' class in case the fan isn't moving at all. By cloning it to your workspace, you can also retrain the in-sensor AI to work for other machinery such as motors or pumps.\nTo use this example, make sure the board is firmly affixed to the front side of the fan, that is, the side that is pushing the air out. For accurate classification, the board's buttons should be facing outward (away from the fan), and the side with the USB port should face toward the ground.",
